dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5115  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"To determine whether SENP1 colocalizes with synaptic markers, we cultured primary hippocampal neurons.\n...\nwe identified an area of neuronal processes and performed 3D-SIM (Figure 1B) [45,46]. This technique bypasses the diffraction limits of optical microscopes to reach a resolution of about 100 nm laterally to match the size of synapses [47,48,49,50]. Profile analysis of single loci suggests that SENP1 and synaptophysin colocalize in neuronal processes (Figure 1C,D). To confirm the co-localization results, we decided to perform a similar experiment using a second SENP1 primary antibody. Similarly to our first analysis, we found that SENP1 can localize with synaptophysin (Supplemental Figure S1A).\n...\nTo determine whether SENP1 also localizes with post-synaptic markers, we co-stained neurons with antibodies against SENP1, MAP2, and the post-synaptic marker drebrin [52] (Figure 1G-I). Intensity profiles of 3D-SIM images suggest that, in neuronal processes, SENP1 can also localize with drebrin (Figure 1J). We confirmed the results using a second antibody against SENP1 (Supplemental Figure S1B).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Primary hippocampal neurons were prepared as previously described by Colnaghi et al., 2019 [36]. Briefly, the dissected hippocampi were obtained from two-day-old CD1 mice.\"\n\nantibodies:\nSENP1 (C-12, Santa Cruz, sc-271360)\nSENP6 (79-M, Santa Cruz, sc-100585)\nSENP7 (E-8, Santa Cruz, sc-373821)\nmicrotubule-associated protein 2 (Map2) (Abcam, AB5392)\nsynaptophysin (Synaptic System, GmbH101002)\ndrebrin (Vinci-Biochem, BSR-M05530)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5115" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

